# TideFS block-volume kernel module Kbuild.
#
# This file builds the tidefs-block-kmod crate as an out-of-tree
# Rust-for-Linux kernel module against Linux 7.0.
#
# Build command (from repo root):
#   make -j8 -C <linux-7.0-src> LLVM=1 O=<linux-7.0-build> M=crates/tidefs-block-kmod MO=<module-out> RUSTC=<rustc> RUSTC_BOOTSTRAP=1 modules
#
# The module defaults to pool-required backend selection and refuses to
# register /dev/tidefs when /dev/tidefs_pool_member cannot be opened. Smoke
# tests that intentionally need the in-memory backend must pass:
#   RUSTFLAGS_MODULE=--cfg=tidefs_block_kmod_bringup_backend
#
# Prerequisites:
#   - Linux 7.0 kernel build tree with CONFIG_RUST=y
#   - modules_prepare completed (builds rust/kernel.o, rust/pin_init.o, etc.)
#   - bindgen available for Rust binding generation
#   - rustc 1.78+ with rust-src component

obj-m := tidefs_block_kmod.o

# Strict warning policy: -Wall -Wextra enables broad diagnostics; -Werror
# promotes warnings to errors so the CI gate catches regressions.
# -Wno-unused-parameter is allowed because kernel APIs and Rust FFI shims
# routinely receive context parameters (e.g. struct block_device *) that
# are forwarded to later layers and intentionally unused here.
subdir-ccflags-y := -Wall -Wextra -Werror -Wno-unused-parameter

# Treat Rust warnings as errors in kernel module builds.
# Clippy lints are the primary Rust quality gate; -Dwarnings ensures the
# build does not silently accrete new warnings.
RUSTFLAGS_MODULE := -Dwarnings
